The '''Nokia Lumia 2520''' is Nokia's first [[Windows RT]] [[tablet computer]], and its first tablet computer since the [[Nokia Internet tablet]] range.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/10/22/nokia-puzzling-windows-tablet-debut/ | title=Nokia<U+2019>s New Tablet Arrives Ahead of Microsoft Deal | publisher=The New York Times | date=22 October 2013 | accessdate=24 October 2013 | author=Wingfield, Nick}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Chang |first=Alexandra |url=http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2013/10/nokia-world/ |title=Nokia World: First Windows Tablet, Big Lumia Phone, and Instagram (Finally) &#124; Gadget Lab |publisher=Wired.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-24  |archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20131022082307/http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2013/10/nokia-world/ |archivedate=22 October 2013}}</ref> It was announced on 22 October 2013 in [[Abu Dhabi]] at the [[Nokia World]] event, during which the company also unveiled the [[Nokia Lumia 1320|Lumia 1320]] and [[Nokia Lumia 1520|Lumia 1520]] [[smartphone]]s.<ref name=TheAustralian>{{Cite news |author=Griffith, Chris |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/technology/nokia-announces-its-first-tablet-the-lumia-2520-and-two-6-inch-phablets/story-e6frgakx-1226744848012 |title=Nokia announces its first tablet, the Lumia 2520, and two 6-inch 'phablets'  |newspaper=The Australian|date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013}}</ref> It was announced after months of media speculation that Nokia would unveil a new tablet.<ref>{{cite web |author=Westaway, Luke |url=http://crave.cnet.co.uk/mobiles/nokia-lumia-2520-is-a-10-1-inch-tablet-with-windows-8-1-rt-50012554/ |title=Nokia Lumia 2520 is a 10.1-inch tablet with Windows 8.1 RT |work=CNET |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/GlJLi |archivedate=24 October 2013}}</ref> The Lumia 2520 will be released in the United States on November 22.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nokia Lumia 2520 Release November 22|url=http://tabletmonkeys.com/nokia-lumia-2520-release-november-22/|publisher=Tabletmonkeys}}</ref> With the United Kingdom and [[Finland]], with other countries "to follow shortly after. It will compete against the [[Microsoft Surface 2]] and [[iPad]].

The Lumia will cost [[United States dollar|US$]]499 while the keyboard will cost US$150.<ref name=CNET>{{cite web |author=Byrne, Seamus |url=http://www.cnet.com.au/nokia-goes-large-with-the-10-1-inch-lumia-2520-tablet-339345750.htm |title=Nokia goes large with the 10.1-inch Lumia 2520 tablet |work=CNET |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/gcfCw |archivedate=24 October 2013}}</ref><ref name=TechRadar>{{cite web |author=Beavis, Gareth |url=http://www.techradar.com/reviews/pc-mac/tablets/nokia-lumia-2520-1191348/review?src=rss&attr=all |title=Hands on: Nokia Lumia 2520 review |work=TechRadar |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013}}</ref>

==Hardware==
The Lumia 2520 will come with a [[4G LTE]] and [[near field communication]] connectivity and a 6.7-megapixel rear-facing camera. The tablet will be released with Windows RT 8.1 installed, features a Full&nbsp;HD (1920<U+00D7>1080) resolution display, and is powered by a [[Snapdragon 800]] [[system on a chip]] which has an integrated Krait 400 quad-core CPU running at 2.2&nbsp;GHz, and an Adreno 330 GPU for graphics.<ref name=PCPRO>{{cite web |author=Ghosh, Shona |url=http://www.pcpro.co.uk/news/384874/nokia-lumia-2520-tablet-arrives-ahead-of-new-ipad |title=Nokia Lumia 2520 tablet arrives ahead of new iPad |work=PC Pro |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013}}</ref>

===Accessories===
Like the Surface 2, Nokia has designed a detachable keyboard called the ''Nokia Power Keyboard'' that is outfitted with two [[USB 2.0]] ports and a battery that is expected to extend the tablet's eleven-hour endurance by five hours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://conversations.nokia.com/2013/10/22/all-in-one-the-nokia-lumia-2520-tablet/ |title=All-in-one: the Nokia Lumia 2520 tablet |publisher=Conversations Nokia |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=25 October 2013 |archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20131022081328/http://conversations.nokia.com/2013/10/22/all-in-one-the-nokia-lumia-2520-tablet/ |archivedate=22 October 2013}}</ref> The keyboard wraps around the rear of the tablet, and so serves as a protective cover.

==Software==
The device is marketed as a hybrid entertainment and productivity device, and will come with [[Microsoft]]'s [[Microsoft Office|Office]] [[Office suite|productivity suite]].<ref>{{Cite news |author=Gibbs, Samuel |url=http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/oct/22/nokia-tablet-lumia-2520-windows-rt |title=Nokia launches Lumia 2520 <U+2013> its first tablet |work=The Guardian |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2013 |archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20131023102631/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/oct/22/nokia-tablet-lumia-2520-windows-rt |archivedate=23 October 2013}}</ref> Also bundled with the tablet will be two of Nokia's proprietary apps <U+2013> ''Nokia Storyteller'' and ''Nokia Video Director''. The Lumia 2520 will also offer the company's [[Here (Nokia)|HERE]] map app and [[Nokia Music]].<ref name=TheAustralian/><ref name=CNET/>

==Reception==
Early reviews have praised the tablet for its display and design.<ref name=TechRadar/><ref>{{cite web |author=Warren, Tom |url=http://www.theverge.com/2013/10/22/4862952/nokia-lumia-2520-windows-tablet-hands-on-photos-video |title=Nokia Lumia 2520: a closer look at Nokia's first Windows tablet |work=The Verge |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=22 October 2013 |archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20131022080817/http://www.theverge.com/2013/10/22/4862952/nokia-lumia-2520-windows-tablet-hands-on-photos-video |archivedate=22 October 2013}}</ref>

